<% content_for :meta_description do %>Security settings, MFA, custom roles, and permissions in <%= installation_brand_name %>.<% end %>

<h1>Security & roles</h1>
<p class="lead">
  Protect workspace access with authentication policies, custom roles, and audit visibility.
</p>

<h2>Default roles</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Administrator</strong> — full settings, billing, user management, all conversations</li>
  <li><strong>Agent</strong> — handle assigned conversations; limited or no settings access</li>
</ul>

<h2>Custom roles (Enterprise)</h2>
<p><strong>Settings → Custom roles</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>Create roles with granular permissions (e.g. manage knowledge base, view reports only)</li>
  <li>Assign custom role when inviting agents</li>
  <li>Examples: <code>knowledge_base_manage</code>, conversation manage, settings view</li>
</ul>
<p>Use custom roles to let senior agents edit Help Center without full admin access.</p>

<h2>Security settings</h2>
<p><strong>Settings → Security</strong> (availability varies)</p>
<ul>
  <li>Password requirements</li>
  <li>Session timeout</li>
  <li>Allowed login methods</li>
  <li>SSO / SAML on Enterprise deployments</li>
</ul>

<h2>Multi-factor authentication (MFA)</h2>
<ol>
  <li>User opens <strong>Profile settings</strong></li>
  <li>Enable MFA / authenticator app</li>
  <li>Scan QR code and save backup codes</li>
</ol>
<p>Admins may enforce MFA org-wide on some plans.</p>

<h2>Sign in with Google</h2>
<p>Optional OAuth login for agents. Does not grant mailbox access unless Gmail inbox is separately connected. See <a href="<%= guide_page_path('workspace-setup') %>">Workspace setup</a>.</p>

<h2>API tokens</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Personal access tokens for API scripts — rotate regularly</li>
  <li>Bot tokens for agent bots — keep secret on your server only</li>
  <li>Revoke tokens when integrations decommissioned</li>
</ul>

<h2>Audit logs</h2>
<p><strong>Settings → Audit logs</strong> records:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Settings changes</li>
  <li>User login/logout</li>
  <li>Account configuration updates</li>
</ul>
<p>Use for compliance reviews and investigating unauthorized changes.</p>

<h2>Data access principles</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Agents see conversations only for inboxes they collaborate on</li>
  <li>Export customer data only with policy approval</li>
  <li>Remove agent access promptly when staff leave — disable or delete user</li>
</ul>

<h2>Reporting security issues</h2>
<p>Contact your operator at <a href="mailto:info@samabrains.com">info@samabrains.com</a> for vulnerability reports affecting your hosted installation.</p>

